### Solution:
If you want to reverse a linked list, you can use a stack. You start with a new stack. You add the nodes in the linked list to the stack. Then you pop them out of the stack and link them back together. 

    public static Node reverse_linked_list(Node node) {
        Stack<Node> stack = new Stack<Node>();
        Node previousnode = null;
        while (node != null) {
            stack.push(node);
            node = node.getSuccessor();
        }
        node = stack.pop();
        previousnode = node;
        while (!stack.isEmpty()) {
            previousnode.setSuccessor(stack.pop());
            previousnode = previousnode.getSuccessor();
        }
        previousnode.setSuccessor(null);
        return previousnode;
    }

